2. **Act to progress the score.**  
   - *Open* any closed doors or cabinets that contain items.  
   - *Take* any item that is present and can be picked up.  
   - *Read* any note or inscription that provides new information.  
   - *Press* any button or lever that could alter a location or unlock a path.  
   - If an object is not directly accessible, *examine* it to see if it reveals another action (e.g., a hidden key or another door).

3. **Move through the world.**  
   - When a room is finished (no new actions give a score), choose the *unexplored* exit direction (north, south, east, west, northeast, southwest, etc.) and *move* there.  
   - If an exit is blocked or leads back to a visited room, try a different unexplored exit from the current location.

4. **Avoid wasteful repetition.**  
   - Skip *look* or *examine* commands if the description is identical to the previous turn.  
   - Do not repeat *open*, *take*, *read*, *press*, or *enter* on the same object unless the environment has changed (e.g., a door that was closed is now open).  
   - If you receive “you can’t see any such thing” or “you can’t go that way” twice, abandon that action and choose a new exit or object.

